`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The `collectTargets()` method uses `included && hasChange` intersection — not just `included`. This is intentional: sending an API write for an MR where nothing would change is wasteful. The preview widget thus doubles as both a user selection tool AND an idempotency gate. mrr-qtk.4 (the dispatch task) gets `BatchPreviewConfirmedMsg.Targets` which is already pre-filtered to only "actionable" MRs.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

